# HTTP Status Codes

| Code | Meaning            |
| ---- | ------------------ |
| 200  | Request successful |
| 201  | Resource created   |
| 400  | Validation error   |
| 401  | Unauthenticated    |
| 404  | Resource not found |
| 500  | Server error       |

---

# Validation Rules

Order Placement:

* Quantity must be greater than 0
* Quantity must not exceed available stock
* Products must be active
* If any product is invalid, the order will fail

---

# Background Jobs

Order confirmation emails are sent using Laravel queue jobs.

Job:

```
SendOrderConfirmationEmail
```

Mailable:

```
OrderConfirmationMail
```

The job is dispatched after successful order placement.
